A suspect has been taken into custody after a woman&#8217;s body was found on Monday. CAPE TOWN - Three women have been murdered in separate attacks in Cape Town over the past few days.The incidents again highlight the country's disturbingly high rate of gender violence as the country and world marks 16 Days of Activism campaign.Thembeka Dumani was shot and killed in the Marikana informal settlement in Philippi East.The motive behind her murder is unknown.In Khayelitsha, Nopinki Fuba's body was found dumped near a communal toilet in Site B.She was allegedly killed by her boyfriend, who has since been arrested and is expected to appear in court on Thursday. on Wednesday, Sigcine Mdani appeared in the Blue Downs Magistrates Court in connection with the murder of Noluvo Swelindawo, in an apparent hate crime.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)